        "title": "How To Create A Drop-Down Navigation Bar With Just Plain CSS",
        "slug": "create-drop-navigation-bar-just-plain-css",
        "markdown": "\nDrop-down navigation are quite handy when it comes to displaying multiple categories of a particular family or a class, also it saves us a lot of space and lines.  \n Drop-downs earlier were made using Javascript or Jquery which usually triggered a the drop-down when clicked on a particular link, but with CSS3 its merely a few lines of code and relief from the ugly looking Javascript.\n\n**What else ?** the CSS based drop-down navigation loads much faster than the Javascript ones and are easily customize-able. In this tutorial we will create the drop-down with just CSS.\n\n**Difficulty : **Intermediate **Things You’ll need :**\n\n- A Text Editor (I prefer Sublime-Text)\n- Browser (obviously)\n- Determination.\n\n**Download the source files [here](http://naveensingh.net/source/dropdown-menu-css.zip) and Go Here For the [Demo](http://naveensingh.net/source/dropdown-menu-css/index.html)**\n\n \n\n[![How-To-Create-A-Drop-Down-Navigation-Bar-With-Just-Plain-CSS](http://i2.wp.com/uiuxblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/How-To-Create-A-Drop-Down-Navigation-Bar-With-Just-Plain-CSS.png?fit=469%2C440)](http://i1.wp.com/uiuxblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/How-To-Create-A-Drop-Down-Navigation-Bar-With-Just-Plain-CSS.png)\n\n\n",
        "html": "<p>Drop-down navigation are quite handy when it comes to displaying multiple categories of a particular family or a class, also it saves us a lot of space and lines. <br />\n Drop-downs earlier were made using Javascript or Jquery which usually triggered a the drop-down when clicked on a particular link, but with CSS3 its merely a few lines of code and relief from the ugly looking Javascript.</p>\n\n<p><strong>What else ?</strong> the CSS based drop-down navigation loads much faster than the Javascript ones and are easily customize-able. In this tutorial we will create the drop-down with just CSS.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Difficulty : <em>*Intermediate *</em>Things You’ll need :</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A Text Editor (I prefer Sublime-Text)</li>\n<li>Browser (obviously)</li>\n<li>Determination.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Download the source files <a href=\"http://naveensingh.net/source/dropdown-menu-css.zip\">here</a> and Go Here For the <a href=\"http://naveensingh.net/source/dropdown-menu-css/index.html\">Demo</a></strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i1.wp.com/uiuxblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/How-To-Create-A-Drop-Down-Navigation-Bar-With-Just-Plain-CSS.png\"><img src=\"http://i2.wp.com/uiuxblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/How-To-Create-A-Drop-Down-Navigation-Bar-With-Just-Plain-CSS.png?fit=469%2C440\" alt=\"How-To-Create-A-Drop-Down-Navigation-Bar-With-Just-Plain-CSS\" title=\"\" /></a></p>",
