        "title": "Ghost - A New Blogging Platform in Town",
        "slug": "ghost-a-new-blogging-platform-in-town",
        "markdown": "\nWelcome the latest blogging platform called [Ghost](http://ghost.org). Blogging is been around from a long time and we have a number of blogging platforms like WordPress,Tumblr,Blogger and many more. Out of the wordpress, blogger, drupal,joomla can be used on your own web hosting as well.\n\nAll these are doing just fine but according to the Founder of [Ghost](http://Ghost.org)  a new blogging platform, WordPress is loosing its touch as a blogging platform and focusing more as a website platform other than its emphasis on blogging, as yourself is that so ? at least I don’t think so because you can do both things with WordPress you can blog as well as run a full-fledged website.\n\n![Ghost - A New Blogging Platform in Town ](http://uiuxblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Welcome-the-new-Blogging-Platform-called-Ghost.png\")\n\nAnyhow, I happened to check out the [Ghost](http://ghost.org)   installed it on my local machine and first impressions were really great here’s what i felt :\n\n- Its easy to setup.\n- Simple and intuitive admin panel\n- installation to up and running takes only 5 minutes\n- its open source\n- easy to add new articles\n- Its responsive too\n\n[Ghost](http://ghost.org) had quite good campaign on [Kickstarter](http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/johnonolan/ghost-just-a-blogging-platform/) and had received investments of almost £200,000 which is about £175,000 more than their requirement which was just £25,000.\n\nBut here’s something I disliked about [Ghost](http://ghost.org) :\n\n- Its still under development\n- Released to the masses quite early\n- The developer community is awefully small and has to be dependent on the help section of [Ghost](http://ghost.org).(but will increase gradually)\n- Cannot be installed on a shared hosting (this will hurt a lot I believe)\n- you’ll need to but a VPS hosting which supports Node.Js\n- Alternatively you can use it on Heroku or other app hosting services.\n\nLooking at the fact that its still under development but will evolve as a great platform and has a great team of powerful Investors including Envato, WooThemes, Internet Explorer etc.\n\nMay be you’ll see my blog running on [Ghost](http://ghost.org) soon.\n\nStay tuned for more on [Ghost](http://ghost.org)\n\n**Meanwhile Check out these themes I made :**\n\n- [Frosty | An Ajax Driven Theme ($5)](https://gum.co/frosty)\n- [Pristine | A Minimalistic Ghost Blogging Theme (free)](http://naveensingh.net/pristine)\n\n\n",
        "html": "<p>Welcome the latest blogging platform called <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a>. Blogging is been around from a long time and we have a number of blogging platforms like WordPress,Tumblr,Blogger and many more. Out of the wordpress, blogger, drupal,joomla can be used on your own web hosting as well.</p>\n\n<p>All these are doing just fine but according to the Founder of <a href=\"http://Ghost.org\">Ghost</a>  a new blogging platform, WordPress is loosing its touch as a blogging platform and focusing more as a website platform other than its emphasis on blogging, as yourself is that so ? at least I don’t think so because you can do both things with WordPress you can blog as well as run a full-fledged website.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://uiuxblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Welcome-the-new-Blogging-Platform-called-Ghost.png\"\" alt=\"Ghost - A New Blogging Platform in Town \" /></p>\n\n<p>Anyhow, I happened to check out the <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a>   installed it on my local machine and first impressions were really great here’s what i felt :</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Its easy to setup.</li>\n<li>Simple and intuitive admin panel</li>\n<li>installation to up and running takes only 5 minutes</li>\n<li>its open source</li>\n<li>easy to add new articles</li>\n<li>Its responsive too</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a> had quite good campaign on <a href=\"http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/johnonolan/ghost-just-a-blogging-platform/\">Kickstarter</a> and had received investments of almost £200,000 which is about £175,000 more than their requirement which was just £25,000.</p>\n\n<p>But here’s something I disliked about <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a> :</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Its still under development</li>\n<li>Released to the masses quite early</li>\n<li>The developer community is awefully small and has to be dependent on the help section of <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a>.(but will increase gradually)</li>\n<li>Cannot be installed on a shared hosting (this will hurt a lot I believe)</li>\n<li>you’ll need to but a VPS hosting which supports Node.Js</li>\n<li>Alternatively you can use it on Heroku or other app hosting services.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Looking at the fact that its still under development but will evolve as a great platform and has a great team of powerful Investors including Envato, WooThemes, Internet Explorer etc.</p>\n\n<p>May be you’ll see my blog running on <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a> soon.</p>\n\n<p>Stay tuned for more on <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Meanwhile Check out these themes I made :</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://gum.co/frosty\">Frosty | An Ajax Driven Theme ($5)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://naveensingh.net/pristine\">Pristine | A Minimalistic Ghost Blogging Theme (free)</a></li>\n</ul>",
