        "title": "How to install Ghost On a Windows PC",
        "slug": "how-to-install-ghost-on-a-windows-pc",
        "markdown": "\nWe introduced the [Ghost](http://ghost.org) app in our previous [article](http://uiuxblog.com/welcome-new-blogging-platform-called-ghost/) its about time for you to try [Ghost](http://ghost.org). Here We’ll see how to install Ghost on a windows PC, so lets begin straight away.\n\n**Difficulty : **Intermediate **Things You’ll need :**\n\n- Node.Js (download it [here](http://nodejs.org/))\n- You’ll need to sign-up on  [Ghost](http://ghost.org)\n- Download the  [Ghost](http://ghost.org) package\n- Determination\n\n**Once you’ve signed up lets start.**\n\n1. [Ghost](http://ghost.org)<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> app is written in Node.js so it won’t work with installing it, I assume you’ve downloaded the Node.js if you haven’t  download the package and install.</span>\n2. If you’ve signed in with  [Ghost](http://ghost.org) you’ll see a big download button, download the package and unzip it in any directory you’d like.\n3. Now goto start and search for Node.js Command prompt, it should look like this\n\n[![How to install Ghost On a Windows PC](http://i1.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/node.png)](http://i1.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/node.png)  \n\nNow type here\n\n```\n    C:\\Users\\Naveen> cd Downloads/ghost-0.3.2\n```\n\nHere downloads is the folder in which I extracted the Ghost package I Downloaded while the ghost-0.3.2 is the folder in which all the contents are present. type the above command and hit enter this will take you in the Ghost’s folder\n\nOnce there, type in\n\n```\n     C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2> dir\n```\n\nand hit enter again you’ll the contents of the folder.\n\nNext step is to install Ghost to do that type\n\n```\n    C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2>npm install --production\n```\n\nand hit enter again.\n\nYou’ll see some process running, once its done you’ll see this line.\n\n```\n    C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2>\n```\n\nNext step is to type.\n\n```\n     C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2>npm start\n```\n\nonce you do this, you’ll see this :\n\n[![how to install ghost blogging platform](http://i0.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/nodej.png)](http://i0.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/nodej.png)\n\nAnd that’s about it goto [http://127.0.0.1:2368](http://127.0.0.1:2368) or [http://localhost:2368](http://localhost:2368) in your browser and experience [Ghost](http://ghost.org)\n\nTo restart the Ghost server open up the Node.js Command prompt and type in\n\n```\n    C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2>npm start\n```\n\nand to close it just hit control+c .\n\n[Download this GIF](http://naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/install-ghost-win-2.gif) to see installation more clearly.\n\nStay tuned for more on [Ghost](http://ghost.org)\n\n\n",
        "html": "<p>We introduced the <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a> app in our previous <a href=\"http://uiuxblog.com/welcome-new-blogging-platform-called-ghost/\">article</a> its about time for you to try <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a>. Here We’ll see how to install Ghost on a windows PC, so lets begin straight away.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Difficulty : <em>*Intermediate *</em>Things You’ll need :</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Node.Js (download it <a href=\"http://nodejs.org/\">here</a>)</li>\n<li>You’ll need to sign-up on  <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a></li>\n<li>Download the  <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a> package</li>\n<li>Determination</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Once you’ve signed up lets start.</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> app is written in Node.js so it won’t work with installing it, I assume you’ve downloaded the Node.js if you haven’t  download the package and install.</span>  </li>\n<li>If you’ve signed in with  <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a> you’ll see a big download button, download the package and unzip it in any directory you’d like.  </li>\n<li>Now goto start and search for Node.js Command prompt, it should look like this</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i1.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/node.png\"><img src=\"http://i1.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/node.png\" alt=\"How to install Ghost On a Windows PC\" title=\"\" /></a>  </p>\n\n<p>Now type here</p>\n\n<pre><code>    C:\\Users\\Naveen&gt; cd Downloads/ghost-0.3.2\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Here downloads is the folder in which I extracted the Ghost package I Downloaded while the ghost-0.3.2 is the folder in which all the contents are present. type the above command and hit enter this will take you in the Ghost’s folder</p>\n\n<p>Once there, type in</p>\n\n<pre><code>     C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2&gt; dir\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and hit enter again you’ll the contents of the folder.</p>\n\n<p>Next step is to install Ghost to do that type</p>\n\n<pre><code>    C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2&gt;npm install --production\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and hit enter again.</p>\n\n<p>You’ll see some process running, once its done you’ll see this line.</p>\n\n<pre><code>    C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Next step is to type.</p>\n\n<pre><code>     C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2&gt;npm start\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>once you do this, you’ll see this :</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i0.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/nodej.png\"><img src=\"http://i0.wp.com/naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/nodej.png\" alt=\"how to install ghost blogging platform\" title=\"\" /></a></p>\n\n<p>And that’s about it goto <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:2368\">http://127.0.0.1:2368</a> or <a href=\"http://localhost:2368\">http://localhost:2368</a> in your browser and experience <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a></p>\n\n<p>To restart the Ghost server open up the Node.js Command prompt and type in</p>\n\n<pre><code>    C:\\Users\\Naveen\\Downloads\\ghost-0.3.2&gt;npm start\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and to close it just hit control+c .</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://naveensingh.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/install-ghost-win-2.gif\">Download this GIF</a> to see installation more clearly.</p>\n\n<p>Stay tuned for more on <a href=\"http://ghost.org\">Ghost</a></p>",
