        "markdown": "\n**Fit.js Free Plugin** is a simple and lightweight javascript plugin that help you **fit *things* into other *things***.  \n Released by [soulwire](https://github.com/soulwire)  \n**Fit uses CSS3 transforms by default, but you can transform the element however you want, for example…**\n\nfit( bar, foo, function( transform ) { var style = window.getComputedStyle( bar ); var size = parseFloat( style.fontSize ); var top = parseFloat( style.marginTop ); bar.style.marginTop = top + transform.ty + 'px'; bar.style.fontSize = size * transform.scale + 'px'; });\n\n[View Demo](http://soulwire.github.io/fit.js/) [View On Github](https://github.com/soulwire/fit.js)\n\n[![Fit.js Free Plugin](http://i0.wp.com/uiuxblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/fit-js-plugin-codextuts.jpg?resize=580%2C380)](http://soulwire.github.io/fit.js/)\n\n\n",
